# Two-clock circuit with an internal clock mux, used for testing
# create_clock with set_clock_groups -logically_exclusive.
#
# clk_fast and clk_slow enter on separate primary input ports and are
# routed to a .names clock mux. The mux output drives the flip-flop
# clock pins, so both clock trees are physically present in the design
# simultaneously — the mux merely selects which one propagates.
#
# Because VPR's clock auto-detection traces back through .names elements
# to root primary inputs, clk_fast and clk_slow are the recognized clock
# source pins. The two clocks are defined on those ports without -add
# (different ports → no -add needed) and marked logically_exclusive.

.model add_clock_logically_exclusive
.inputs in1 in2 sel clk_fast clk_slow
.outputs out1 out2

# Clock mux: sel=0 selects clk_fast, sel=1 selects clk_slow.
# Both clock trees are physically present in the fabric simultaneously.
.names sel clk_fast clk_slow clk_mux_out
0 1 - 1
1 - 1 1

.latch to_FFA FFA re clk_mux_out 0
.latch to_FFB FFB re clk_mux_out 0

# Combinational path from FFA output into FFB's data input, creating
# a register-to-register timing path within each clock domain.
.names FFA in2 to_FFB
11 1

.names in1 to_FFA
1 1

.names FFA out1
1 1

.names FFB out2
1 1

.end
